description: This file is a header (.h) file defining the interface for HTTP Webc Session objects, including function prototypes for creation, removal, and initialization of session objects, specific to an HTTP implementation within a broader system.

methods.name: HttpCreateWebcSession
methods.description: Creates a new Webc Session object with specified container, owner, and reserved handles.

methods.name: HttpWcsoCreate
methods.description: Creates a Webc Session object, initializing its internal structure.

methods.name: HttpWcsoRemove
methods.description: Removes a Webc Session object, freeing associated resources.

methods.name: HttpWcsoEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls necessary internal objects or dependencies for the Webc Session.

methods.name: HttpWcsoInitialize
methods.description: Initializes the Webc Session object to a default or configured state.
